{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BBjRgoxyvtnnoauMdorFCo","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here is a summary of what was implemented:\n\n**Files changed:**\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/stack-detect.ts` — Added `Cargo.toml` check to `detectStack()`, added `RUST_WEB_FRAMEWORKS` and `RUST_AGENT_DEPS` constants, added Rust block to `detectAppType()` with priority order: agent > server > cli > library/generic.\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/stack-detect.test.ts` — Added 14 new test cases covering: Rust stack detection (including workspace), Rust app type detection for cli/server/agent/library/generic, priority ordering (agent over server), negative cases (no Cargo.toml), and priority vs Node.js/Python.\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-1-rust-stack-and-app-type-detection.md` — Status changed to `review`, all 7 ACs checked off.\n\n**Test results:** 50/50 passing (was 36 before, added 14 Rust tests).\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Code quality concern:** Cargo.toml parsing uses simple string `includes()` matching, not a proper TOML parser. This is per spec (NFR4 — no TOML parser dependency), but it means a dependency name appearing in a comment or in `[dev-dependencies]` would match. For example, `# we considered using axum` in a comment would trigger server detection. The story explicitly calls for this approach, but it's worth noting as tech debt if precision matters later.\n- **Observation:** The existing test for \"unrecognized stack\" was using `'rust'` as the unrecognized stack. Changed it to `'java'` since Rust is now recognized. This is correct but worth noting in case anyone references that test expectation.\n- **Observation:** AC4 says library detection should return `'generic'` — the story maps library crates to the existing `generic` AppType rather than introducing a new `'library'` type. This is a deliberate design choice in the spec, not a bug, but means library crates are indistinguishable from truly unrecognized projects in downstream logic."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ad2222ca243524826 (use SendMessage with to: 'ad2222ca243524826' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 23632\ntool_uses: 14\nduration_ms: 86936</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6b184f1a-3a3f-4307-8da0-d8cf52066851","uuid":"0054c1b9-7f88-4ca4-bc4d-f31dedb7b5fe","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:11:11.175Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-1-rust-stack-and-app-type-detection.md — implement all tasks, write tests, and mark the story for review. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously through all tasks until complete. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (build failures, test failures, unclear task specs, missing APIs)\n- Workarounds applied (anything hacky, copied patterns that felt wrong, TODOs left behind)\n- Code quality concerns (areas that need refactoring, edge cases not handled, tech debt added)\n- Observations (unexpected complexity, architectural mismatches, dependency issues)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"ad2222ca243524826","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here is a summary of what was implemented:\n\n**Files changed:**\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/stack-detect.ts` — Added `Cargo.toml` check to `detectStack()`, added `RUST_WEB_FRAMEWORKS` and `RUST_AGENT_DEPS` constants, added Rust block to `detectAppType()` with priority order: agent > server > cli > library/generic.\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/stack-detect.test.ts` — Added 14 new test cases covering: Rust stack detection (including workspace), Rust app type detection for cli/server/agent/library/generic, priority ordering (agent over server), negative cases (no Cargo.toml), and priority vs Node.js/Python.\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-1-rust-stack-and-app-type-detection.md` — Status changed to `review`, all 7 ACs checked off.\n\n**Test results:** 50/50 passing (was 36 before, added 14 Rust tests).\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Code quality concern:** Cargo.toml parsing uses simple string `includes()` matching, not a proper TOML parser. This is per spec (NFR4 — no TOML parser dependency), but it means a dependency name appearing in a comment or in `[dev-dependencies]` would match. For example, `# we considered using axum` in a comment would trigger server detection. The story explicitly calls for this approach, but it's worth noting as tech debt if precision matters later.\n- **Observation:** The existing test for \"unrecognized stack\" was using `'rust'` as the unrecognized stack. Changed it to `'java'` since Rust is now recognized. This is correct but worth noting in case anyone references that test expectation.\n- **Observation:** AC4 says library detection should return `'generic'` — the story maps library crates to the existing `generic` AppType rather than introducing a new `'library'` type. This is a deliberate design choice in the spec, not a bug, but means library crates are indistinguishable from truly unrecognized projects in downstream logic."}],"totalDurationMs":86936,"totalTokens":23632,"totalToolUseCount":14,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":233,"cache_read_input_tokens":22848,"output_tokens":550,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":233},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
