{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UrsWACEgNx3cQjKftiWn4D","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good. Here is the review summary.\n\n---\n\n**CODE REVIEW FINDINGS**\n\n**Story:** 8-1-rust-stack-and-app-type-detection\n**Git vs Story Discrepancies:** 0\n**Issues Found:** 2 High, 5 Medium, 1 Low\n\n### HIGH issues (fixed)\n\n1. **False positive on `[dev-dependencies]` and `[build-dependencies]`** -- `cargoContent.includes(dep)` searched the entire Cargo.toml file, so agent/server deps in `[dev-dependencies]` or `[build-dependencies]` would incorrectly trigger detection. Fixed by adding `getCargoDepsSection()` to extract only the `[dependencies]` section.\n\n2. **Substring false positives on crate names** -- `cargoContent.includes('anthropic')` matched `anthropic-sdk`, `cargoContent.includes('rocket')` matched `sprocket`. Fixed by adding `hasCargoDep()` with word-boundary regex (`dep` followed by `=` or `{`).\n\n### MEDIUM issues (fixed)\n\n3. **`[[bin]]` and `[lib]` matched inside comments** -- `cargoContent.includes('[[bin]]')` would match `# not a [[bin]]`. Fixed by using `^\\[\\[bin\\]\\]\\s*$/m` regex requiring the section header to be on its own line.\n\n4. **Missing test for `[lib]` + `[[bin]]` combo** -- Added test confirming `[[bin]]` takes priority (returns `cli`).\n\n5. **Missing tests for `rocket`, `warp`, `tide` web frameworks** -- Only `axum` and `actix-web` had tests. Added tests for all three missing frameworks.\n\n6. **Missing false-positive prevention tests** -- Added tests for: substring match on `anthropic-sdk`, substring match on `sprocket`, agent dep in `[dev-dependencies]`, agent dep in `[build-dependencies]`, web framework in `[dev-dependencies]`, `[[bin]]` in comment.\n\n7. **No `[build-dependencies]` isolation** -- Same root cause as #1. Fixed by the `getCargoDepsSection()` approach.\n\n### LOW issues (not fixed)\n\n8. **No TOML-aware inline table parsing** -- `getCargoDepsSection()` uses simple section-header regex. A Cargo.toml with unusual formatting (e.g., `[dependencies.serde]` subsection style) would not be captured by the current `[dependencies]` section extractor. Acceptable per tech spec NFR4 (\"no TOML parser dependency\").\n\n### Results after fixes\n\n- **Tests:** 60 pass in stack-detect (was 50), 2954 pass full suite\n- **Coverage:** 97.02% overall, all 123 files above 80% floor\n- **Story status:** Updated to `verifying`\n\n### Files modified\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/stack-detect.ts` -- Added `getCargoDepsSection()`, `hasCargoDep()`, replaced naive `includes()` with section-aware + boundary-aware matching, replaced `includes('[[bin]]')` / `includes('[lib]')` with line-anchored regexes\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/stack-detect.test.ts` -- Added 10 new tests for false-positive prevention, missing framework coverage, and edge cases\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-1-rust-stack-and-app-type-detection.md` -- Status changed from `review` to `verifying`\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and their severity:**\n- HIGH: `[dev-dependencies]`/`[build-dependencies]` deps incorrectly matched as production deps (false positive agent/server detection) -- FIXED\n- HIGH: Substring false positives on crate names (`anthropic` matching `anthropic-sdk`, `rocket` matching `sprocket`) -- FIXED\n- MEDIUM: `[[bin]]` and `[lib]` matched inside TOML comments -- FIXED\n- MEDIUM: Missing test coverage for 3 of 5 web frameworks (rocket, tide, warp) -- FIXED\n- MEDIUM: Missing test for `[lib]` + `[[bin]]` dual-crate pattern -- FIXED\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority, tech debt):**\n- `getCargoDepsSection()` does not handle `[dependencies.foo]` inline subsection TOML style. Acceptable per NFR4 (no TOML parser). Would only matter for rare Cargo.toml formatting.\n- Python `hasPythonDep()` and Rust `hasCargoDep()` share a similar pattern (regex word-boundary matching) but are not unified. Minor duplication; the regex patterns differ enough that unification adds complexity for little gain.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- No integration test exercising `detectStack()` -> `detectAppType()` end-to-end (both are unit tested independently; acceptable).\n- No test for Cargo.toml with `[workspace]` + deps (workspace detection returns `rust` from `detectStack` but app type detection for workspace root with deps is not specifically tested beyond standard dep matching).\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. The implementation follows the existing pattern (stack-specific if/else blocks) exactly as other stacks do.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed and verified."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a1ef095ce6c9f9b26 (use SendMessage with to: 'a1ef095ce6c9f9b26' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 51435\ntool_uses: 31\nduration_ms: 178246</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6b184f1a-3a3f-4307-8da0-d8cf52066851","uuid":"1e705a9b-be14-406c-9c54-89b6dfdd114d","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:14:35.457Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-1-rust-stack-and-app-type-detection.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Bugs found and their severity (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW with brief description)\n- Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt)\n- Coverage gaps (files below floor, untested e