{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JUJfU45hNETebPpjF61yiZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 8-2: Expand State Types for Rust\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer,\n     8→I want the harness state to support Rust-specific fields,\n     9→So that coverage tool and OTLP config are correctly stored without type errors.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given a Rust project is initialized, when state is written, then `coverage.tool` accepts `'cargo-tarpaulin'` without type errors <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given a Rust project has OTLP configured, when state is written, then `otlp.rust_env_hint` field is present with value `'OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→\n    16→## Technical Notes\n    17→\n    18→### State Interface\n    19→\n    20→File: `src/lib/state.ts` — `HarnessState` interface.\n    21→\n    22→Two changes needed:\n    23→\n    24→1. **Coverage tool type union**: Change `coverage.tool` type from `'c8' | 'coverage.py' | 'unknown'` to `'c8' | 'coverage.py' | 'cargo-tarpaulin' | 'unknown'`. This is referenced in `src/lib/coverage.ts` as `CoverageToolInfo.tool` — both must be updated consistently.\n    25→\n    26→2. **OTLP rust_env_hint**: Add optional `rust_env_hint?: string` to the OTLP state section. This stores `'OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT'` for Rust projects.\n    27→\n    28→### Breaking Change Risk\n    29→\n    30→None. All additions are optional fields or type union expansions. Existing Node.js and Python state files are unaffected.\n    31→\n    32→### State Storage Format\n    33→\n    34→The state file is YAML frontmatter in `.claude/codeharness.local.md`. No migration needed — new fields are optional.\n    35→\n    36→### Tests\n    37→\n    38→Verify TypeScript compilation passes with `cargo-tarpaulin` assigned to `coverage.tool` and `rust_env_hint` assigned to OTLP state. Add type assertion tests if existing test patterns support it.\n    39→\n    40→## Files to Change\n    41→\n    42→- `src/lib/state.ts` — Expand `HarnessState.coverage.tool` type union to include `'cargo-tarpaulin'`, add optional `rust_env_hint?: string` to OTLP state section\n    43→- `src/lib/coverage.ts` — Expand `CoverageToolInfo.tool` type union to include `'cargo-tarpaulin'` (must match state.ts)\n    44→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BsKgFqrbnadEhsJTw9WBFH","session_id":"6b184f1a-3a3f-4307-8da0-d8cf52066851","uuid":"474a25f1-42d0-4233-b453-818bf64e54e5","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:19:20.854Z"}
