{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TGQjcs3823g1WAshsVNPZJ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 8-2: Expand State Types for Rust\n     2→\n     3→## Status: review\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer,\n     8→I want the harness state to support Rust-specific fields,\n     9→So that coverage tool and OTLP config are correctly stored without type errors.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [x] AC1: Given a Rust project is initialized, when state is written, then `coverage.tool` accepts `'cargo-tarpaulin'` without type errors <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [x] AC2: Given a Rust project has OTLP configured, when state is written, then `otlp.rust_env_hint` field is present with value `'OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→\n    16→## Technical Notes\n    17→\n    18→### State Interface\n    19→\n    20→File: `src/lib/state.ts` — `HarnessState` interface.\n    21→\n    22→Two changes needed:\n    23→\n    24→1. **Coverage tool type union**: Change `coverage.tool` type from `'c8' | 'coverage.py' | 'unknown'` to `'c8' | 'coverage.py' | 'cargo-tarpaulin' | 'unknown'`. This is referenced in `src/lib/coverage.ts` as `CoverageToolInfo.tool` — both must be updated consistently.\n    25→\n    26→2. **OTLP rust_env_hint**: Add optional `rust_env_hint?: string` to the OTLP state section. This stores `'OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT'` for Rust projects.\n    27→\n    28→### Breaking Change Risk\n    29→\n    30→None. All additions are optional fields or type union expansions. Existing Node.js and Python state files are unaffected.\n    31→\n    32→### State Storage Format\n    33→\n    34→The state file is YAML frontmatter in `.claude/codeharness.local.md`. No migration needed — new fields are optional.\n    35→\n    36→### Tests\n    37→\n    38→Verify TypeScript compilation passes with `cargo-tarpaulin` assigned to `coverage.tool` and `rust_env_hint` assigned to OTLP state. Add type assertion tests if existing test patterns support it.\n    39→\n    40→## Files to Change\n    41→\n    42→- `src/lib/state.ts` — Expand `HarnessState.coverage.tool` type union to include `'cargo-tarpaulin'`, add optional `rust_env_hint?: string` to OTLP state section\n    43→- `src/lib/coverage.ts` — Expand `CoverageToolInfo.tool` type union to include `'cargo-tarpaulin'` (must match state.ts)\n    44→\n    45→## Tasks/Subtasks\n    46→\n    47→- [x] Task 1: Expand `coverage.tool` type union in `HarnessState` (state.ts) from `string` to `'c8' | 'coverage.py' | 'cargo-tarpaulin' | 'unknown'`\n    48→- [x] Task 2: Expand `CoverageToolInfo.tool` type union in coverage.ts to include `'cargo-tarpaulin'`\n    49→- [x] Task 3: Add optional `rust_env_hint?: string` to OTLP state section in state.ts\n    50→- [x] Task 4: Update `getCoverageTool()` in docs-scaffold.ts to return `'cargo-tarpaulin'` for rust stack\n    51→- [x] Task 5: Write type assertion and round-trip tests for cargo-tarpaulin and rust_env_hint\n    52→- [x] Task 6: Run full test suite — 2961 tests pass, zero regressions\n    53→\n    54→## Dev Agent Record\n    55→\n    56→### Implementation Plan\n    57→\n    58→- Expand `HarnessState.coverage.tool` from generic `string` to a proper type union `'c8' | 'coverage.py' | 'cargo-tarpaulin' | 'unknown'` (was previously untyped)\n    59→- Expand `CoverageToolInfo.tool` in coverage.ts to match the same union\n    60→- Add optional `rust_env_hint?: string` to the OTLP section of `HarnessState`\n    61→- Update `getCoverageTool()` to map `'rust'` stack to `'cargo-tarpaulin'`\n    62→- Add comprehensive tests: type assertions, YAML round-trip, optional field behavior\n    63→\n    64→### Completion Notes\n    65→\n    66→All acceptance criteria satisfied. TypeScript compilation passes for all modified files. The `coverage.tool` type was tightened from `string` to a proper union, which is a stricter (non-breaking) change. The `getCoverageTool()` function in docs-scaffold.ts was also updated to handle `'rust'` stack correctly. Full test suite: 113 files, 2961 tests, all passing.\n    67→\n    68→## File List\n    69→\n    70→- `src/lib/state.ts` — Modified: expanded `coverage.tool` type to union, added `rust_env_hint` to OTLP\n    71→- `src/lib/coverage.ts` — Modified: expanded `CoverageToolInfo.tool` type to include `'cargo-tarpaulin'`\n    72→- `src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` — Modified: updated `getCoverageTool()` return type and added rust mapping\n    73→- `src/lib/__tests__/state.test.ts` — Modified: added 5 tests for Rust type support (cargo-tarpaulin, rust_env_hint)\n    74→- `src/lib/__tests__/coverage.test.ts` — Modified: added CoverageToolInfo type assertion test for cargo-tarpaulin\n    75→- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/docs-scaffold.test.ts` — Modified: added getCoverageTool rust test\n    76→\n    77→## Change Log\n    78→\n    79→- 2026-03-23: Expanded state types for Rust stack support — coverage.tool union includes cargo-tarpaulin, OTLP section includes rust_env_hint, getCoverageTool maps rust to cargo-tarpaulin\n    80→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01CGkWizVB7CtGCqwFm5rfNr","session_id":"6b184f1a-3a3f-4307-8da0-d8cf52066851","uuid":"1c404fed-ea69-4d1b-8610-f6b4a1dc1a00","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:22:51.695Z"}
