{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CGkWizVB7CtGCqwFm5rfNr","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**Review Complete.**\n\n**Story:** 8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust\n**Status:** `verifying`\n**Tests:** 2968 passing (7 new), 0 regressions\n**Coverage:** 97.03% overall (target 90%), all 123 files above 80% per-file floor\n\n**Files modified during review:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/state.ts` — Added `getDefaultCoverageTool()` so `getDefaultState()` sets correct coverage tool per stack\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/coverage.ts` — Added rust branch in `detectCoverageTool()`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` — Added rust support in `getStackLabel()` and `generateAgentsMdContent()`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/state.test.ts` — 3 new tests for stack-dependent coverage tool defaults\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/coverage.test.ts` — 1 new test for Cargo.toml detection\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/__tests__/docs-scaffold.test.ts` — 3 new tests for rust stack label and AGENTS.md content\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust.md` — Status updated to `verifying`, review notes added\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and fixed:**\n- **HIGH**: `getDefaultState()` hardcoded `coverage.tool` to `'c8'` regardless of stack parameter. Rust projects initialized via `codeharness init` would get `c8` as their default coverage tool instead of `cargo-tarpaulin`.\n- **MEDIUM**: `detectCoverageTool()` had no rust branch. A Cargo.toml project would fall through to `'unknown'` tool, making `codeharness coverage` non-functional for Rust.\n- **MEDIUM**: `getStackLabel('rust')` returned `'Unknown'` — AGENTS.md scaffold would mislabel Rust projects.\n- **MEDIUM**: `generateAgentsMdContent()` had no rust branch — Rust projects got \"No recognized stack\" boilerplate instead of Cargo commands.\n- **MEDIUM**: Missing tests for rust paths in `detectCoverageTool`, `getStackLabel`, `generateAgentsMdContent`, and `getDefaultState`.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- Git diff shows `sprint-state.json` and `.session-issues.md` modified but not listed in story File List. Cosmetic documentation gap.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- `parseCoverageReport` has no `'tarpaulin-json'` parser — it will return 0 for Rust projects. This is out of scope for story 8-2 (type expansion only) but will need addressing in a later story for end-to-end Rust coverage reporting.\n- Type-only files (`src/types/state.ts`, `src/types/observability.ts`, `src/types/index.ts`, `src/modules/verify/types.ts`, `src/modules/verify/verification-ac-types.ts`, `src/modules/verify/verification-runner-types.ts`) show 0% coverage — these are pure type/interface exports with no runtime code, so 0% is expected.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- `getCoverageTool()` in `docs-scaffold.ts` and `getDefaultCoverageTool()` in `state.ts` duplicate the stack-to-tool mapping. Consider consolidating into a single source of truth (e.g., a shared `stackConfig` map). Not urgent — two call sites is manageable.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues were fixed in this review."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aaea0d6cccd307169 (use SendMessage with to: 'aaea0d6cccd307169' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 63144\ntool_uses: 33\nduration_ms: 189297</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6b184f1a-3a3f-4307-8da0-d8cf52066851","uuid":"94f79f1a-a2a1-4fef-aaa4-d21e1c17074d","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:25:53.873Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Bugs found and their severity (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW with brief description)\n- Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt)\n- Coverage gaps (files below floor, untested edge cases, areas needing integration tests)\n- Architecture concerns (patterns that don't fit, coupling issues, missing abstractions)\n- Items sent back for re-development (what failed and why)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"aaea0d6cccd307169","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**Review Complete.**\n\n**Story:** 8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust\n**Status:** `verifying`\n**Tests:** 2968 passing (7 new), 0 regressions\n**Coverage:** 97.03% overall (target 90%), all 123 files above 80% per-file floor\n\n**Files modified during review:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/state.ts` — Added `getDefaultCoverageTool()` so `getDefaultState()` sets correct coverage tool per stack\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/coverage.ts` — Added rust branch in `detectCoverageTool()`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` — Added rust support in `getStackLabel()` and `generateAgentsMdContent()`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/state.test.ts` — 3 new tests for stack-dependent coverage tool defaults\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/coverage.test.ts` — 1 new test for Cargo.toml detection\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/__tests__/docs-scaffold.test.ts` — 3 new tests for rust stack label and AGENTS.md content\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust.md` — Status updated to `verifying`, review notes added\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and fixed:**\n- **HIGH**: `getDefaultState()` hardcoded `coverage.tool` to `'c8'` regardless of stack parameter. Rust projects initialized via `codeharness init` would get `c8` as their default coverage tool instead of `cargo-tarpaulin`.\n- **MEDIUM**: `detectCoverageTool()` had no rust branch. A Cargo.toml project would fall through to `'unknown'` tool, making `codeharness coverage` non-functional for Rust.\n- **MEDIUM**: `getStackLabel('rust')` returned `'Unknown'` — AGENTS.md scaffold would mislabel Rust projects.\n- **MEDIUM**: `generateAgentsMdContent()` had no rust branch — Rust projects got \"No recognized stack\" boilerplate instead of Cargo commands.\n- **MEDIUM**: Missing tests for rust paths in `detectCoverageTool`, `getStackLabel`, `generateAgentsMdContent`, and `getDefaultState`.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- Git diff shows `sprint-state.json` and `.session-issues.md` modified but not listed in story File List. Cosmetic documentation gap.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- `parseCoverageReport` has no `'tarpaulin-json'` parser — it will return 0 for Rust projects. This is out of scope for story 8-2 (type expansion only) but will need addressing in a later story for end-to-end Rust coverage reporting.\n- Type-only files (`src/types/state.ts`, `src/types/observability.ts`, `src/types/index.ts`, `src/modules/verify/types.ts`, `src/modules/verify/verification-ac-types.ts`, `src/modules/verify/verification-runner-types.ts`) show 0% coverage — these are pure type/interface exports with no runtime code, so 0% is expected.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- `getCoverageTool()` in `docs-scaffold.ts` and `getDefaultCoverageTool()` in `state.ts` duplicate the stack-to-tool mapping. Consider consolidating into a single source of truth (e.g., a shared `stackConfig` map). Not urgent — two call sites is manageable.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues were fixed in this review."}],"totalDurationMs":189297,"totalTokens":63144,"totalToolUseCount":33,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":797,"cache_read_input_tokens":61349,"output_tokens":997,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":797},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
